The paper deals with the creation of a backbone in a wireless network, which falls under the category of networked systems (cs.NI). The backbone is created using a connected dominating set, which is a common technique in distributed computing (cs.DC) and graph theory (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the Signal-to-Interference-plus-Noise-Ratio (SINR) model, which is a popular model for wireless communication and falls under the category of information theory (cs.IT) and signal processing (cs.SI).
